National Treasury Director-General Mr Dondo Mogajane JOHANNESBURG - Former Treasury Director-General, Dondo Mogajane, has been appointed chairperson of the Government Employees Pension Fund board. The GEPF Board of Trustees held its first meeting on Tuesday. READ:Â Dondo Mogajane leaves Treasury In a statement, Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana, also congratulated Eddie Kekana, who was elected as deputy chairperson of the pension fund. The minister thanked the outgoing board for its service. Godongwana emphasised the need for the incoming board to continue to lead the fund with care and judiciousness during the challenging economic climate.